      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why a Formal Exception Process Matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without a documented exception process, budget overages resolve themselves in one of two unsatisfactory ways: the guardrail blocks production traffic and an engineer disables it to restore service (bypassing all financial controls), or the overage is absorbed silently and the team learns nothing. A formal exception process provides a third path \u2014 a structured, time-bounded approval workflow that maintains financial oversight while allowing legitimate overages to proceed with appropriate authorisation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The process also serves as a signal. A team requesting its third exception in six months has a budget that is structurally too low, not a sequence of exceptional circumstances. Tracking exception frequency converts an ad-hoc workaround into a data-driven input for the annual budget re-baseline."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Exception Approval Process",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request Form Requirements"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The exception request form is the contract between the team and the approver. It must collect enough information for the approver to make a decision without a back-and-forth, and it must record the team's commitments \u2014 which creates accountability for post-approval follow-through."
          }
        ]
      },
