      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from __future__ import annotations\nimport datetime, uuid\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nclass Urgency(Enum):\n    P0 = \"p0\"   # production currently impacted\n    P1 = \"p1\"   # SLA at risk within 4 hours\n    P2 = \"p2\"   # planned need, no immediate impact\n\nclass ExceptionStatus(Enum):\n    PENDING            = \"pending\"\n    AWAITING_INFO      = \"awaiting_info\"\n    APPROVED           = \"approved\"\n    DENIED             = \"denied\"\n    EXPIRED            = \"expired\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass BudgetExceptionRequest:\n    request_id:         str = field(default_factory=lambda: str(uuid.uuid4()))\n    submitted_at:       str = field(\n        default_factory=lambda: datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n    )\n    team:               str = \"\"\n    cost_centre:        str = \"\"\n    requestor:          str = \"\"\n    current_spend_usd:  float = 0.0\n    monthly_cap_usd:    float = 0.0\n    extra_budget_usd:   float = 0.0   # requested overage amount\n    duration_days:      int   = 0\n    urgency:            Urgency = Urgency.P2\n    business_justification: str = \"\"\n    root_cause:         str = \"\"\n    optimisation_plan:  str = \"\"\n    estimated_roi:      Optional[str] = None\n    status:             ExceptionStatus = ExceptionStatus.PENDING\n    approver:           Optional[str] = None\n    decision_at:        Optional[str] = None\n    decision_notes:     Optional[str] = None\n\n    def is_valid(self) -> tuple[bool, list[str]]:\n        errors = []\n        if not self.business_justification.strip():\n            errors.append(\"business_justification is required\")\n        if not self.root_cause.strip():\n            errors.append(\"root_cause is required\")\n        if not self.optimisation_plan.strip():\n            errors.append(\"optimisation_plan is required\")\n        if self.extra_budget_usd <= 0:\n            errors.append(\"extra_budget_usd must be positive\")\n        if self.duration_days <= 0 or self.duration_days > 30:\n            errors.append(\"duration_days must be 1\u201330\")\n        if self.extra_budget_usd > 5_000 and not self.estimated_roi:\n            errors.append(\"estimated_roi is required for overages above $5,000\")\n        return len(errors) == 0, errors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Approval Authority Matrix"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The approver is determined by two axes: the dollar amount of the requested overage and the urgency. P0 requests bypass the standard SLA and route directly to a human on-call approver with a 2-hour response commitment. Non-urgent requests follow the standard 24-hour SLA."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass ApprovalRoute:\n    approver_role: str\n    sla_hours:     int\n    requires_roi:  bool\n\ndef route_exception(request: BudgetExceptionRequest) -> ApprovalRoute:\n    extra = request.extra_budget_usd\n    urgent = request.urgency in (Urgency.P0, Urgency.P1)\n    if extra <= 500:\n        return ApprovalRoute(\n            approver_role = \"finops-lead\",\n            sla_hours     = 0,    # auto-approved by bot\n            requires_roi  = False,\n        )\n    if extra <= 5_000:\n        return ApprovalRoute(\n            approver_role = \"engineering-director\",\n            sla_hours     = 2 if urgent else 24,\n            requires_roi  = False,\n        )\n    if extra <= 25_000:\n        return ApprovalRoute(\n            approver_role = \"vp-engineering\",\n            sla_hours     = 2 if urgent else 24,\n            requires_roi  = True,\n        )\n    return ApprovalRoute(\n        approver_role = \"cfo\",\n        sla_hours     = 4 if urgent else 48,\n        requires_roi  = True,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executing the Approval: Issuing the Override"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the approver approves a request, two things must happen atomically: the budget cap in Redis is raised by the approved extra amount, and an immutable audit record is written to the exception log. The atomic step matters \u2014 a cap raise without an audit record is an unexplained gap in the financial record; an audit record without a cap raise leaves the guardrail firing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import datetime, json\nimport boto3\nimport redis\n\n_redis = redis.Redis(host=\"redis\", port=6379, decode_responses=True)\n_ddb   = boto3.resource(\"dynamodb\")\n\nEXCEPTION_LOG_TABLE = \"budget-exception-log\"\nCENTS               = 100_000\n\ndef approve_exception(\n    request:      BudgetExceptionRequest,\n    approver:     str,\n    decision_notes: str = \"\",\n) -> BudgetExceptionRequest:\n    valid, errors = request.is_valid()\n    if not valid:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Cannot approve invalid request: {errors}\")\n\n    # 1. Raise the Redis cap atomically\n    month     = datetime.datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y-%m\")\n    cap_key   = f\"budget_cap:{request.team}:{month}\"\n    extra_micro = int(request.extra_budget_usd * CENTS)\n    _redis.incrby(cap_key, extra_micro)\n\n    # 2. Write immutable audit record to DynamoDB\n    table = _ddb.Table(EXCEPTION_LOG_TABLE)\n    table.put_item(Item={\n        \"request_id\":      request.request_id,\n        \"team\":            request.team,\n        \"submitted_at\":    request.submitted_at,\n        \"decided_at\":      datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"approver\":        approver,\n        \"decision\":        \"approved\",\n        \"extra_budget_usd\": str(request.extra_budget_usd),\n        \"duration_days\":   request.duration_days,\n        \"root_cause\":      request.root_cause,\n        \"optimisation_plan\": request.optimisation_plan,\n        \"decision_notes\":  decision_notes,\n    })\n\n    request.status      = ExceptionStatus.APPROVED\n    request.approver    = approver\n    request.decision_at = datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n    return request\n\ndef deny_exception(\n    request:      BudgetExceptionRequest,\n    approver:     str,\n    reason:       str,\n) -> BudgetExceptionRequest:\n    table = _ddb.Table(EXCEPTION_LOG_TABLE)\n    table.put_item(Item={\n        \"request_id\":  request.request_id,\n        \"team\":        request.team,\n        \"submitted_at\": request.submitted_at,\n        \"decided_at\":  datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"approver\":    approver,\n        \"decision\":    \"denied\",\n        \"denial_reason\": reason,\n    })\n    request.status      = ExceptionStatus.DENIED\n    request.approver    = approver\n    request.decision_at = datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n    request.decision_notes = reason\n    return request"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mandatory Post-Approval Follow-Through"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Approving a budget exception without requiring follow-through converts the process into a rubber stamp. Two mandatory actions apply to every approved exception:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Optimisation plan execution: "
                  },
                  "the team must implement (or formally defer with reason) the optimisation plan they committed to in the request form within 30 days. FinOps tracks this via a backlog item created automatically at approval time."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Post-mortem for P0/P1 triggers: "
                  },
                  "if the exception was triggered by a P0 or P1 event, a root-cause document must be filed within three business days explaining how the event caused the overage and what prevents recurrence."
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n@dataclass\nclass OptimisationCommitment:\n    request_id:         str\n    team:               str\n    plan_description:   str\n    due_date:           str   # ISO date\n    status:             str = \"open\"   # open / completed / deferred\n    completion_notes:   str = \"\"\n\ndef create_optimisation_backlog_item(\n    request: BudgetExceptionRequest,\n) -> OptimisationCommitment:\n    import datetime\n    due = (\n        datetime.date.today() + datetime.timedelta(days=30)\n    ).isoformat()\n    commitment = OptimisationCommitment(\n        request_id       = request.request_id,\n        team             = request.team,\n        plan_description = request.optimisation_plan,\n        due_date         = due,\n    )\n    # Persist to FinOps backlog (e.g. Linear, Jira, or internal DB)\n    # finops_backlog.create(commitment)\n    return commitment\n\ndef flag_repeat_offenders(\n    exception_log: list[dict],\n    lookback_months: int = 6,\n    threshold: int = 3,\n) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return teams with >= threshold approved exceptions in lookback_months.\"\"\"\n    import datetime\n    from collections import defaultdict\n    cutoff = (\n        datetime.datetime.utcnow() - datetime.timedelta(days=lookback_months * 30)\n    ).isoformat()\n    counts: dict[str, int] = defaultdict(int)\n    for record in exception_log:\n        if record.get(\"decision\") == \"approved\" and record[\"decided_at\"] >= cutoff:\n            counts[record[\"team\"]] += 1\n    return [team for team, count in counts.items() if count >= threshold]"
          }
        ]
